title: AttributeError: 'AttrDict' object has no attribute 'gst'

labels.name: wontfix
labels.description: This will not be worked on

body:
I cloned this repo, installed the dependencies in a conda environment, installed jupyterlab, and tried to execute the notebook `DDC_TTS_and_MultiBand_MelGAN_Example.ipynb`. However, I ran into the following error:

```
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AttributeError                            Traceback (most recent call last)
/var/folders/v4/r2mn8r996rg_frh4kx_z_cq40000gn/T/ipykernel_3741/3401549502.py in <module>
      6 # load the model
      7 num_chars = len(phonemes) if TTS_CONFIG.use_phonemes else len(symbols)
----> 8 model = setup_model(num_chars, len(speakers), TTS_CONFIG)
      9 
     10 # load model state

~/repos/TTS/TTS/tts/utils/generic_utils.py in setup_model(num_chars, num_speakers, c, speaker_embedding_dim)
     83                         decoder_output_dim=c.audio['num_mels'],
     84                         gst=c.use_gst,
---> 85                         gst_embedding_dim=c.gst['gst_embedding_dim'],
     86                         gst_num_heads=c.gst['gst_num_heads'],
     87                         gst_style_tokens=c.gst['gst_style_tokens'],

AttributeError: 'AttrDict' object has no attribute 'gst'
```

I believe the `config.json` file that is downloaded in the first cell has outdated or incorrect information. Any advice about how to resolve this?
